moves.name: Ice Spinner
moves.desc: Ends the effects of Electric Terrain, Grassy Terrain, Misty Terrain, and Psychic Terrain.
moves.shortDesc: Ends the effects of terrain.

moves.name: Belly Drum
moves.desc: Raises the user's Attack by 12 stages in exchange for the user losing 1/2 of its maximum HP, rounded down. Fails if the user would faint or if its Attack stat stage is 6.
moves.shortDesc: User loses 50% max HP. Maximizes Attack.

moves.name: Liquidation
moves.desc: Has a 20% chance to lower the target's Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 20% chance to lower the target's Defense by 1.

moves.name: Protect
moves.desc: The user is protected from most attacks made by other Pokemon during this turn. This move has a 1/X chance of being successful, where X starts at 1 and triples each time this move is successfully used. X resets to 1 if this move fails, if the user's last move used is not Baneful Bunker, Burning Bulwark, Detect, Endure, King's Shield, Max Guard, Obstruct, Protect, Quick Guard, Silk Trap, Spiky Shield, or Wide Guard, or if it was one of those moves and the user's protection was broken. Fails if the user moves last this turn.
moves.shortDesc: Prevents moves from affecting the user this turn.

moves.name: Ice Shard
moves.desc: No additional effect.
moves.shortDesc: Usually goes first.

moves.name: Earthquake
moves.desc: Damage doubles if the target is using Dig.
moves.shortDesc: Hits adjacent Pokemon. Double damage on Dig.

moves.name: High Horsepower
moves.desc: No additional effect.
moves.shortDesc: No additional effect.

moves.name: Play Rough
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to lower the target's Attack by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to lower the target's Attack by 1.

moves.name: Heavy Slam
moves.desc: The power of this move depends on (user's weight / target's weight), rounded down. Power is equal to 120 if the result is 5 or more, 100 if 4, 80 if 3, 60 if 2, and 40 if 1 or less. Damage doubles and no accuracy check is done if the target has used Minimize while active.
moves.shortDesc: More power the heavier the user than the target.

moves.name: Icicle Crash
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to make the target flinch.
moves.shortDesc: 30% chance to make the target flinch.

moves.name: Superpower
moves.desc: Lowers the user's Attack and Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the user's Attack and Defense by 1.

moves.name: Knock Off
moves.desc: If the target is holding an item that can be removed from it, ignoring the Sticky Hold Ability, this move's power is multiplied by 1.5. If the user has not fainted, the target loses its held item. This move cannot cause Pokemon with the Sticky Hold Ability to lose their held item or cause a Kyogre, a Groudon, a Giratina, an Arceus, a Genesect, a Silvally, a Zacian, or a Zamazenta to lose their Blue Orb, Red Orb, Griseous Orb, Plate, Drive, Memory, Rusted Sword, or Rusted Shield respectively. Items lost to this move cannot be regained with Recycle or the Harvest Ability.
moves.shortDesc: 1.5x damage if foe holds an item. Removes item.

moves.name: Body Slam
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to paralyze the target. Damage doubles and no accuracy check is done if the target has used Minimize while active.
moves.shortDesc: 30% chance to paralyze the target.

moves.name: Tera Blast
moves.desc: If the user is Terastallized, this move becomes a physical attack if the user's Attack is greater than its Special Attack, including stat stage changes, and this move's type becomes the same as the user's Tera Type. In addition, if the user's Tera Type is Stellar, this move has 100 power, is super effective against Terastallized targets and neutral against other targets, and lowers the user's Attack and Special Attack by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: If Terastallized: Phys. if Atk > SpA, type = Tera.

moves.name: Ice Punch
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to freeze the target.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to freeze the target.

moves.name: Double-Edge
moves.desc: If the target lost HP, the user takes recoil damage equal to 33% the HP lost by the target, rounded half up, but not less than 1 HP.
moves.shortDesc: Has 33% recoil.

moves.name: Avalanche
moves.desc: Power doubles if the user was hit by the target this turn.
moves.shortDesc: Power doubles if user is damaged by the target.

moves.name: Rest
moves.desc: The user falls asleep for the next two turns and restores all of its HP, curing itself of any non-volatile status condition in the process. Fails if the user has full HP, is already asleep, or if another effect is preventing sleep.
moves.shortDesc: User sleeps 2 turns and restores HP and status.

moves.name: Bulldoze
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to lower the target's Speed by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 100% chance lower adjacent Pkmn Speed by 1.

moves.name: Body Press
moves.desc: Damage is calculated using the user's Defense stat as its Attack, including stat stage changes. Other effects that modify the Attack stat are used as normal.
moves.shortDesc: Uses user's Def stat as Atk in damage calculation.

moves.name: Stomping Tantrum
moves.desc: Power doubles if the user's last move on the previous turn, including moves called by other moves or those used through Instruct, Magic Coat, Snatch, or the Dancer or Magic Bounce Abilities, failed to do any of its normal effects, not including damage from an unsuccessful High Jump Kick, Jump Kick, or Mind Blown, or if the user was prevented from moving by any effect other than recharging or Sky Drop. A move that was blocked by Baneful Bunker, Detect, King's Shield, Protect, Spiky Shield, Crafty Shield, Mat Block, Quick Guard, or Wide Guard will not double this move's power, nor will Bounce or Fly ending early due to the effect of Gravity, Smack Down, or Thousand Arrows.
moves.shortDesc: Power doubles if the user's last move failed.

moves.name: Icicle Spear
moves.desc: Hits two to five times. Has a 35% chance to hit two or three times and a 15% chance to hit four or five times. If one of the hits breaks the target's substitute, it will take damage for the remaining hits. If the user has the Skill Link Ability, this move will always hit five times.
moves.shortDesc: Hits 2-5 times in one turn.

moves.name: Icy Wind
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to lower the target's Speed by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 100% chance to lower the foe(s) Speed by 1.

moves.name: Curse
moves.desc: If the user is not a Ghost type, lowers the user's Speed by 1 stage and raises the user's Attack and Defense by 1 stage. If the user is a Ghost type, the user loses 1/2 of its maximum HP, rounded down and even if it would cause fainting, in exchange for the target losing 1/4 of its maximum HP, rounded down, at the end of each turn while it is active. If the target uses Baton Pass, the replacement will continue to be affected. Fails if there is no target or if the target is already affected.
moves.shortDesc: Curses if Ghost, else -1 Spe, +1 Atk, +1 Def.

moves.name: Facade
moves.desc: Power doubles if the user is burned, paralyzed, or poisoned. The physical damage halving effect from the user's burn is ignored.
moves.shortDesc: Power doubles if user is burn/poison/paralyzed.

moves.name: Entrainment
moves.desc: Causes the target's Ability to become the same as the user's. Fails if the target's Ability is As One, Battle Bond, Comatose, Disguise, Gulp Missile, Ice Face, Multitype, Power Construct, RKS System, Schooling, Shields Down, Stance Change, Tera Shift, Truant, Zen Mode, or Zero to Hero, or the same Ability as the user, or if the user's Ability is As One, Battle Bond, Comatose, Commander, Disguise, Embody Aspect, Flower Gift, Forecast, Hunger Switch, Ice Face, Illusion, Imposter, Multitype, Neutralizing Gas, Poison Puppeteer, Power Construct, Power of Alchemy, Protosynthesis, Quark Drive, Receiver, RKS System, Schooling, Shields Down, Stance Change, Tera Shell, Tera Shift, Teraform Zero, Trace, Wonder Guard, Zen Mode, or Zero to Hero.
moves.shortDesc: The target's Ability changes to match the user's.

moves.name: Snowscape
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the weather becomes Snow. During the effect, the Defense of Ice-type Pokemon is multiplied by 1.5 when taking damage from a physical attack. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Icy Rock. Fails if the current weather is Snow.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, snow falls. Ice: 1.5x Def.

moves.name: Yawn
moves.desc: Causes the target to fall asleep at the end of the next turn. Fails when used if the target cannot fall asleep or if it already has a non-volatile status condition. At the end of the next turn, if the target is still active, does not have a non-volatile status condition, and can fall asleep, it falls asleep. If the target becomes affected, this effect cannot be prevented by Safeguard or a substitute, or by falling asleep and waking up during the effect.
moves.shortDesc: Puts the target to sleep after 1 turn.

moves.name: Helping Hand
moves.desc: The power of the target's attack this turn is multiplied by 1.5 (this effect is stackable). Fails if there is no ally adjacent to the user or if the ally already moved this turn, but does not fail if the ally is using a two-turn move.
moves.shortDesc: One adjacent ally's move power is 1.5x this turn.

moves.name: Bounce
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to paralyze the target. This attack charges on the first turn and executes on the second. On the first turn, the user avoids all attacks other than Gust, Hurricane, Sky Uppercut, Smack Down, Thousand Arrows, Thunder, and Twister, and Gust and Twister have doubled power when used against it. If the user is holding a Power Herb, the move completes in one turn.
moves.shortDesc: Bounces turn 1. Hits turn 2. 30% paralyze.

moves.name: Substitute
moves.desc: The user takes 1/4 of its maximum HP, rounded down, and puts it into a substitute to take its place in battle. The substitute is removed once enough damage is inflicted on it, or if the user switches out or faints. Baton Pass can be used to transfer the substitute to an ally, and the substitute will keep its remaining HP. Until the substitute is broken, it receives damage from all attacks made by other Pokemon and shields the user from status effects and stat stage changes caused by other Pokemon. Sound-based moves and Pokemon with the Infiltrator Ability ignore substitutes. The user still takes normal damage from weather and status effects while behind its substitute. If the substitute breaks during a multi-hit attack, the user will take damage from any remaining hits. If a substitute is created while the user is trapped by a binding move, the binding effect ends immediately. Fails if the user does not have enough HP remaining to create a substitute without fainting, or if it already has a substitute.
moves.shortDesc: User takes 1/4 its max HP to put in a substitute.

moves.name: Chilling Water
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to lower the target's Attack by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 100% chance to lower the target's Attack by 1.

moves.name: Blizzard
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to freeze the target. If the weather is Snow, this move does not check accuracy.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to freeze foe(s). Can't miss in Snow.

moves.name: Hyper Voice
moves.desc: No additional effect.
moves.shortDesc: No additional effect. Hits adjacent foes.

moves.name: Take Down
moves.desc: If the target lost HP, the user takes recoil damage equal to 1/4 the HP lost by the target, rounded half up, but not less than 1 HP.
moves.shortDesc: Has 1/4 recoil.

moves.name: Sleep Talk
moves.desc: One of the user's known moves, besides this move, is selected for use at random. Fails if the user is not asleep. The selected move does not have PP deducted from it, and can currently have 0 PP. This move cannot select Assist, Beak Blast, Belch, Bide, Blazing Torque, Celebrate, Chatter, Combat Torque, Copycat, Dynamax Cannon, Focus Punch, Hold Hands, Magical Torque, Me First, Metronome, Mimic, Mirror Move, Nature Power, Noxious Torque, Shell Trap, Sketch, Sleep Talk, Struggle, Uproar, Wicked Torque, or any two-turn move.
moves.shortDesc: User must be asleep. Uses another known move.

moves.name: Amnesia
moves.desc: Raises the user's Special Defense by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Raises the user's Sp. Def by 2.

moves.name: Charm
moves.desc: Lowers the target's Attack by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the target's Attack by 2.

moves.name: Giga Impact
moves.desc: If this move is successful, the user must recharge on the following turn and cannot select a move.
moves.shortDesc: User cannot move next turn.

moves.name: Ice Beam
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to freeze the target.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to freeze the target.

moves.name: Ice Fang
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to freeze the target and a 10% chance to make it flinch.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to freeze. 10% chance to flinch.

moves.name: Rain Dance
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the weather becomes Rain Dance. The damage of Water-type attacks is multiplied by 1.5 and the damage of Fire-type attacks is multiplied by 0.5 during the effect. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Damp Rock. Fails if the current weather is Rain Dance.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, heavy rain powers Water moves.

moves.name: Hyper Beam
moves.desc: If this move is successful, the user must recharge on the following turn and cannot select a move.
moves.shortDesc: User cannot move next turn.

abilities.name: Slush Rush
abilities.desc: If Snow is active, this Pokemon's Speed is doubled.
abilities.shortDesc: If Snow is active, this Pokemon's Speed is doubled.

abilities.name: Thick Fat
abilities.desc: If a Pokemon uses a Fire- or Ice-type attack against this Pokemon, that Pokemon's offensive stat is halved when calculating the damage to this Pokemon.
abilities.shortDesc: Fire-/Ice-type moves against this Pokemon deal damage with a halved offensive stat.

abilities.name: Sheer Force
abilities.desc: This Pokemon's attacks with secondary effects have their power multiplied by 1.3, but the secondary effects are removed. If a secondary effect was removed, it also removes the user's Life Orb recoil and Shell Bell recovery, and prevents the target's Anger Shell, Berserk, Color Change, Emergency Exit, Pickpocket, Wimp Out, Red Card, Eject Button, Kee Berry, and Maranga Berry from activating.
abilities.shortDesc: This Pokemon's attacks with secondary effects have 1.3x power; nullifies the effects.

items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -SpD Nature. Single use.

items.name: Rocky Helmet

items.name: Bright Powder

items.name: Room Service
items.desc: If Trick Room is active, the holder's Speed is lowered by 1 stage. Single use.

items.name: Never-Melt Ice

items.name: Metronome

items.name: Muscle Band
items.desc: Holder's physical attacks have 1.1x power.

items.name: Ability Shield

items.name: Salac Berry
items.desc: Raises holder's Speed by 1 stage when at 1/4 max HP or less. Single use.

items.name: Grassy Seed
items.desc: If the terrain is Grassy Terrain, raises holder's Defense by 1 stage. Single use.

items.name: Chople Berry

items.name: Mental Herb
items.desc: Cures holder of Attract, Disable, Encore, Heal Block, Taunt, Torment. Single use.

items.name: Mirror Herb
items.desc: When an opposing Pokemon raises a stat stage, the holder copies it. Single use.

items.name: Electric Seed
items.desc: If the terrain is Electric Terrain, raises holder's Defense by 1 stage. Single use.

items.name: Wiki Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -SpA Nature. Single use.

items.name: Air Balloon
items.desc: Holder is immune to Ground-type attacks. Pops when holder is hit.

items.name: Adrenaline Orb
items.desc: Raises holder's Speed by 1 stage if it gets affected by Intimidate. Single use.

items.name: Red Card
items.desc: If holder survives a hit, attacker is forced to switch to a random ally. Single use.

items.name: Quick Claw
items.desc: Each turn, holder has a 20% chance to move first in its priority bracket.

items.name: Eviolite
items.desc: If holder's species can evolve, its Defense and Sp. Def are 1.5x.

items.name: Babiri Berry
items.desc: Halves damage taken from a supereffective Steel-type attack. Single use.

items.name: Safety Goggles
items.desc: Holder is immune to powder moves and damage from Sandstorm or Hail.

items.name: Charti Berry
items.desc: Halves damage taken from a supereffective Rock-type attack. Single use.
